  "prompt": "How do you determine the year that a VHS tape was produced?",
  "response": "There are several ways to determine the year a VHS tape was produced:\n\n1. Copyright date: Check the tape, box, or sleeve for a copyright year printed on it.\n\n2. Release date: Look for the movie's original theatrical release date if it's a feature film.\n\n3. Manufacturing date stamp: Some VHS tapes have a manufacturing date printed on the cassette itself, often in small print.\n\n4. Video release information: Research when the movie was first released on VHS.\n\n5. Packaging design: The style of the packaging can give clues about the era.\n\n6. Distributor information: Different video distributors were prominent in different time periods.\n\n7. Tracking information on the tape: Sometimes contains production or distribution dates.\n\nIf unsure, you can also research online databases or consult VHS collectors' resources for specific details about a particular tape.",
